${slide:title=What you will learn}$

- Lookup of class methods are the same as instance methods
- Class methods are not (java like) static methods
- Class methods are plain normal methods

${slide:title=There is only One Way}$

When we send messages to an instance, corresponding methods are looked up in the instance class and applied to that instance


${slide:title=Remember: Sending a message}$

${columns}$

${column:width=40}$

Sending a message to an object
- go to the class of the object
- look for the method associated to the message selector
- follow the inheritance chain
- apply the found method to the receiver

