${slide:title=Class is just an instance}$

A class is an object instance of another class (called a metaclass)
- A metaclass is just one class whose instances are classes! 
- ==Counter== is the unique instance of the class ==Counter class==
- ==Counter class== is automatically created when you create the class ==Counter==
- The class of class ==XXX== is named ==XXX class==


